  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hypothesis:

      Sunphenon, a green tea extract containing 95% egcg, given daily as oral medication over a
      period of 18 months has anti-inflammatory and neuroprotective properties in patients with
      relapsing-remitting multiple sclerosis as assessed by magnetic resonance imaging and clinical
      examination (EDSS and MSFC).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This multicentric, national study investigates the efficacy and safety of EGCG in patients
      with relapsing-remitting multiple sclerosis.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
